      <span class="h5">How to re-pressurise your boiler.</span>
      <span class="h1 enlighten">How do I know if I have <b>low boiler pressure?</b></span>
    </h2>
        <p slot="paragraph">The first sign of a low-pressure boiler is if your heating or hot water isn’t working properly. But to find out for sure, check the water pressure gauge on the front on your boiler. This will be either a hydraulic dial or a digital reading.</p>
        <p slot="paragraph">Ideally, the gauge should read between 1 and 1.5. But if it reads less than 1 bar, your boiler pressure is too low and needs re-pressurising.</p>
